y, other things to know about rogues.<br><br>1)  Not all of us like to be called rogues.  We have proper names, actually.  They are as follows:<br><br>Scouts of Kelethin (Wood elf or Half Elves working in Kelethin)<br>Merchants of the Coalition of Tradesfolk Illegal (Humans and Half Elves out of Freeport)<br>Initiates of the Circle of Unseen Hands (Humans and Half Elves out of Qeynos)<br>Initiates of the Ebon Mask (Dark Elves)<br>Members of the White Rose (Barbarians)<br>Family friends of the Deeppockets (Halflings)<br>Deep Muses (Gnomes)<br>Journeymen of the Taruun (Vah Shir).  <br><br>Each from their own group, with different styles.<br><br>2)  We are the sexies class out there.  You've heard of lovable rogues, dashing rogues, etc... but who's ever heard the term dashing shaman? <br><br>3)  Just remember, rogues can do anything.  As I say this, I have just AC buffed a raid, attack buffed myself, and turned into an iksar.<br><br>4)  Did I mention we're sexy?<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel<br>Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/18/02 2:30:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2159.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/miscpics/couple.jpg height=200 width=100.gif></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: so, tell me about...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You've heard of lovable rogues, dashing rogues<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Knight in shining armour?  Tall dark elf and handsome..